Godwin Isenyo, Kaduna The management of Kaduna Electric Company said it would not disconnect electricity consumers in all states under its franchise during the COVID-19 pandemic period. The Head of Corporate Communication of the KAEDCO, Abdullahi Abdulazeez, said this while delivering relief materials donated to the Kaduna State Government on Monday. Abdulazeez said the suspension of disconnection of customers became imperative because of the lockdown over the coronavirus pandemic. The relief materials include 500 bags of parboiled rice, 400 bags of semovita, 100 cartons of indomie noodles and 100 cartons of vegetable oil. Abdulazeez said the items were worth N30m and they would be distributed to its franchise which are Kaduna, Katsina, Kebbi, Sokoto and Zamfara states. Copyright PUNCH.
